  Abstract                 = {We introduce a novel dataset with a news sentiment index that was constructed from a selection of over
300,000 newspaper articles from five of the top ten U.S. newspapers by circulation. By constructing ARMA
models, we show that news and consumer sentiment, when combined with other macroeconomic variables,
achieve statistically significant results to explain changes in private consumption. We make three distinct
