does not. In general, we conclude that news sentiment is a useful variable to add in consumer behavior
models, especially when coupled with consumer sentiment and other macroeconomic variables. Tested individually,
news sentiment is as good a proxy as personal income for explaining private consumption growth
when tested individually.},
